<L>&YOGH;e slen me with &yogh;oure eyen emelye</L>
<L N="1568">&YOGH;e ben the cause wherfore that I deye
<PB REF="00000062.tif" N="46"></L>
<L>Of al the remenaunt of myn o&thorn;er care</L>
<L>Ne sette I not the mountenauns of a tare</L>
<L>So &thorn;at I coude don ou&yogh;t to &yogh;oure plesaunse</L>
<L N="1572">And with &thorn;at word he fyl down in a traunce</L>
<L>A long tyme &amp; aftyrward he vp styrte</L>
<L>This palamoun &thorn;at thoute &thorn;at thorw hese herte</L>
<L>He felte a cold swerd sodeynliche glyde</L>
<L N="1576">ffor yre he quok / no lengere wolde he byde</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;at he hadde herd Arcytis tale<MILESTONE N="153b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As hewere wod with face ded and pale</L>
<L>He styrte hym vp out of the boschis &thorn;ikke</L>
<L N="1580">And seyde arcite false traytour wikke</L>
<L>Now art &thorn;ou hent &thorn;at louyst myn lady so</L>
<L>for whom &thorn;at I haue al &thorn;is peyne and wo</L>
<L>And art myn blod &amp; to myn conseyl sworn</L>
<L N="1584">As I ful oftyn haue seyd &thorn;e here be-forn</L>
