<L>But I wele loue here only &amp; no mo</L>
<L>ffor I am palamoun &thorn;yn mortal fo</L>
<L>And &thorn;ow &thorn;at I no wepene haue in &thorn;is place</L>
<L N="1592">But out of prisoun am styrt by grace</L>
<L>I drede not &thorn;at outher &thorn;ou schat deye<NOTE PLACE="marg">See V. 54.</NOTE></L>
<L>Or &thorn;ou ne schat not louyn emalye</L>
<L>Ches which &thorn;ou wit or &thorn;ou schat not asterte</L>
<L N="1596">This Arcyte with ful dispitous herte</L>
<L>Whan he hym knew &amp; hadde hese tale herd</L>
<L>As fers as lyoun pullede out a swerd</L>
<L>And seyde &thorn;us bi god that set a-boue</L>
<L N="1600">Nere it &thorn;at &thorn;ou art sek &amp; wod for loue</L>
<L>And ek for &thorn;ou no wepen hast in &thorn;is place</L>
<L>Thow schuldist neuere out of &thorn;is grene pase</L>
<L>That &thorn;ou ne schuldist deyen of myn hond</L>
<L N="1604">ffor I defie the surete &amp; the bond<NOTE PLACE="marg">'Love cannot be given up as thou deemest: and he loves but little, who ceases loving in order to keep a promise.' V. 51.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="marg">V. 51.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000063.tif" N="47"></L>
<L>Wiche &thorn;at &thorn;ou seyst &thorn;at I haue mad to &thorn;e</L>
<L>What veray fol &thorn;ink wel that loue is fre<NOTE PLACE="marg">V. 51.</NOTE></L>
<L>And I wele loue here maugre al &thorn;yn my&yogh;t</L>
<L N="1608">But for as meche &thorn;ou art a worthy kny&yogh;t</L>
<L>And wilnyst to darrayne here be batayle</L>
<L>Haue here myn trouthe to-morwe I nyl not fayle</L>
<L>With-oute wetynge of ony o&thorn;er whight</L>
<L N="1612">That here I wele be foundyn as a knyght</L>
<L>And bryngyn harneys ry&yogh;t I-now for the<MILESTONE N="154a" UNIT="folio"></L>
