<L>So wery of &thorn;in lewdenes</L>
<L N="2112">That also wisly god me bles</L>
<L>Myn eres ake of thi darsty speche</L>
<L>Now suche a ryme &thorn;e deuel I be-teche</L>
<L>This may be wel ryme dogerell quod he</L>
<L N="2116">Whi so quod I why wilt &thorn;ou lette me</L>
<L>More of my tale than an other man</L>
<L>Sethyns it is &thorn;e beste ryme I can</L>
<L>By god quod he pleynly I the say</L>
<L N="2120">Thou shalt no lenger rymen here to day</L>
<L>Thow dost noght elles but dyspendest tyme</L>
<L>Sire oo word &thorn;ou shalt no lenger ryme</L>
<L>Let see whe&thorn;er &thorn;ou canst telle ought in geste</L>
<L N="2124">Or telle in prose somwhat at &thorn;e leste</L>
<L>In whiche &thorn;er be somme merthe &amp; som doctrine</L>
<L>Gladly quod I by goddes swete pyne</L>
<L>I wil &yogh;ou telle a litel thing in prose</L>
